      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Hexachlorophene, a substance used in the manufacture of germicidal soaps, is prepared by reaction of 2,4,5-trichlorophenol with formaldehyde in the presence of concentrated sulfuric acid. Propose a mechanism for the reaction.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbWNWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--e5d6173f8ec1cb15df99078baa922975ae0adbd3/OChem_16_EC_025.jpg\" alt=\"Benzene bonded to three chlorine atoms and a hydroxyl group reacts with formaldehyde in the presence of sulfuric acid to form hexachlorophene.\">",
